          <avActivityHighlights>New snow and wind slabs in all aspects. New snow represents the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of new snow and a strong to storm force northeasterly wind, sometimes large wind slabs will form by the evening in particular in places that are protected from the wind. In all aspects medium-sized slab avalanches are possible as a consequence of the snowfall. In particular on wind-loaded slopes the avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack and reach large size in isolated cases.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The old snowpack is largely stable. The new snow will be deposited on a quite favourable old snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
        </BulletinMeasurements>
      </bulletinResultsOf>
    </Bulletin>
